>CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span>). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075126,"guid":"9A9817F0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075125,"previous_guid":"9775A240278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B5AF6EA50D4D459DB35CDB5E49478E93","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prep. and mixing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BBB5694B0C0E467EA82C14FFA611C47F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add the <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">trace metal solution. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075127,"guid":"9FFE1500278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075126,"previous_guid":"9A9817F0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E283C15C27114BB08A5679901F45906C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prep. and mixing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A64B8C673E3443C9A78A8981407CB6E9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add the <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">carbon source <\/span><span>(as defined by your media sheet and\/or microorganism). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"AF4BC3B0FA714AE48F0D360F383A4AF6","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Depending on the nature of the C-source, you might want to add it after the degassing stage. For example, methanol, that can be used for M.barkeri, could have high volatility and be lost during degassing. <\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075128,"guid":"C35F3DD0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075127,"previous_guid":"9FFE1500278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EEF53ACB36CB459EA375501526A99741","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prep. and mixing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"436582D486EA4C21804C87EE0B109D33","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>, an indicator of redox level, if it was not already contained in the <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">salt mix <\/span><span>or <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">buffer solution.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"9640B9D0278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":25,"title":"concentration","source":{"concentration":1,"unit":null,"title":"Resazurin"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075130,"guid":"D48977B0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075128,"previous_guid":"C35F3DD0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F7C451A8A550472CB6879BC8E557BD42","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prep. and mixing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E3438B562C50444E997E4C9A407B677E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Fill up to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> with milliq-H<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>O. Make sure you stop stirring, while topping up to <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, as the stirring can cause you to misjudge the volume. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A2A6B4E0278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"L","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"A526F720278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"L","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075131,"guid":"DA3927F0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075130,"previous_guid":"D48977B0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3A5F22E033BC480782BE9B5749B05C5D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prep. and mixing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"93AF14DA928D44B2A1E0A7609289E5F4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place media flask on a pH-meter and adjust the pH with HCl \/ NaOH (or KOH in case of sodium-free media) to the level required by the specific media.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"99C812E84AC646B8B85E433F5AC1B797","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Once the pH is adjusted, we are ready for the degassing stage. At this point, the 1L media can be split into batches of smaller volume as desired. For example, degassing stage can be quicker for a smaller volume. Also, a 200ml batch can be used to fill 40 Hungate tubes with 5ml each. <\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075132,"guid":"E24B0B20278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075131,"previous_guid":"DA3927F0278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A18B05410B9F454EBD6C635CDBF205E7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"00F7DE59F3424831A0E8402063057A6B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Heat media close to boiling point but try to avoid boiling (as this would increase the loss of solvents). The heating step can entail;<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Placing the flask into a water bath that has been heated to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (works well for Duran flasks). <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>- <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Round neck flasks might be easier to heat on a hot-stirrer plate that has reached the <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> heat-marking.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D4840E90278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"D721C3E0278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":100,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"7A0A0534572E4291B007BFBE73056335","order_id":4,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Option:<\/span><span> Place the\tmedia in\tthe microwave with a stopper and bring\tit just below boiling temperature\tprior to placing it\tin water\tbath or hot stirrer\tplate. This can save time. Experience shows\tthat\tthere\tare no detrimental effects\tof microwave treatment, but note that this might\tchange with specifics\tof the media\tcomposition. If using\tmicrowave,\ta guide is to use\t1 minute per\t100ml of media.\t<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">IMPORTANT: It must be noted that heating in the\tmicrowave can generate a\tvacuum\tin the flask, pulling in the\tstopper.\tTo avoid\tthe stopper being\tfully pulled in, make sure you  loosen it well before putting the flask in the microwave and also pull the stopper out immediately\twhen you get the\tflask out of the microwave\u2013 note that the flask will be hot!<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075134,"guid":"6E62FF00278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075132,"previous_guid":"E24B0B20278311EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A1A787A6A16C4FA0825892824ED39441","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"22B82E31E1A342B89FEE1B35E78FFFBE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Bring the heated flask next to the gassing manifold and set it on a heating\/stirring plate. \n\n\n<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075135,"guid":"768E5DA0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075134,"previous_guid":"6E62FF00278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B5DD77E46FE64B73867D2E0786A91E35","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4636F05709754CCE8594620C19352251","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Insert a redox and temperature probe into the media and the gas-line into the headspace. Secure a stopper in place, to minimize gas exchange between flask and atmosphere. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5E81A30177AB48E78E7026A9D2FDC5B4","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Option: <\/span><span>The use of redox and temperature probes should be optional, however note that the use of Resazurin as redox indicator provides only an estimate of the success of degassing. Resazurin goes colourless at a redox value of -51mV and can interact with certain organics. Having a redox probe would provide an exact measure of redox and hence more information. In our experience, Rezasurin remaining pink correlates well with a media that will not support anaerobic growth but this might change with specifics of media and species. In general, we recommend use of redox probe where possible. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075136,"guid":"889E1580278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075135,"previous_guid":"768E5DA0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7B97542FFF164D3DB6338C2D0808B772","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"58E0B9D74FC24CF5B6DAE6D79E6BFB85","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Turn on the gas cylinder and start gas flow at 1 liters per minute (LPM) using the appropriate gas mixture with your gassing manifold. As a rule of thumb, when the medium contains bicarbonate or carbonate, use a N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>\/CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> (80\/20) mixture, otherwise use 100% N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">A gas flow of 0.5 LPM will be sufficient for 200 mL in round-neck flasks. The gassing setup is shown in Picture 1.<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/dn2ybafcf.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A2D9F8F24DEA49DD96C00E0F5E73720A","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/dn2ybafcf.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075137,"guid":"BE4CE990278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075136,"previous_guid":"889E1580278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"91B2311170ED4C35A90A5926F7785B4E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3F52CC52436241F786D316BF703E4835","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">When the medium has reached 80\u00b0 C, push the gas-line down into the liquid, so it bubbles through the medium. If in step 10, no temperature probe was used, use the water bath or heating plate temperature and the time that the media spent on the heating device as a proxy to judge media temperature. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Note that pushing the gas-line into the liquid would not be possible for 200 mL in round-neck flasks, unless your gas-line\/canula is long enough. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075138,"guid":"CDC38000278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075137,"previous_guid":"BE4CE990278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"88FAEFB019904C2CB63DEC14FBE80742","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2F75158018E14DEFB9C065CEC6CD485F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> - <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> degassing at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>, turn off the heating system and add the <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">vitamin solution<\/span><span>, and <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Cysteine-HCl <\/span><span>(it is assumed here that there are no additional compositional elements but this might change with the specifics of your media). <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"F10F0880278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":300,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"F347BA70278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":600,"title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"F6255EF0278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":900},{"id":1075139,"guid":"D404C1E0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075138,"previous_guid":"CDC38000278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8BCC2EE7B13F457D96FB49023CDAB948","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CFD6078DB2AA420893DE04D185239AAF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Continue gas flow, while the medium is cooling and until a redox value of - 300 mV or less is reached AND the media turns colourless, i.e. the Resazurin dye shifts from pink to colorless. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075140,"guid":"DBEEAAB0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075139,"previous_guid":"D404C1E0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"004F01777A114B08909B7B73CEB0D216","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2C8A8EE900C149768F26076506985DF6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove any probes that are still in the flask. This might cause the media to turn pink. In that case, continue degassing a bit more. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075141,"guid":"E09FAFA0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075140,"previous_guid":"DBEEAAB0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"43C498063ED545BC8FE9387234D06EB2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Heating and degassing stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B03959AA8B3946238C7944060E290707","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the gassing line (while gas is still flowing), by pressing the stopper in place and carefully pulling the gas line (while minimizing any chance of air flow into the flask). Immediately push the stopper fully in place and tape it secure (this is important as moving into the anaerobic chamber in the next step might cause the stopper be displaced due to pressure changes). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075142,"guid":"E5981DD0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075141,"previous_guid":"E09FAFA0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F6994E80B5D44FBDBEAD1D9BCB14372B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"65AFB4E45B744A81A52DF17D361E8174","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Move the flask into the anaerobic chamber air lock and start the gassing sequence without any delay. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075143,"guid":"EF7C01E0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075142,"previous_guid":"E5981DD0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B141860EC0D745ABA649E27370C9E95C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EA5C93703B894192804E189A82BC93DF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Once the airlock cycle is finished, move the flask into the anaerobic chamber. Ideally, you should let the flask in the chamber and wait a bit (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> - <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>) before opening it. This would allow the anaerobic chamber to recover\/equilibrate from the airlock sequence and reach low O<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> levels again. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"0966B900278611EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":600,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"0BC394C0278611EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1200,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":1800},{"id":1075144,"guid":"F583E440278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075143,"previous_guid":"EF7C01E0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0E007E25985E4BF0A7CF6FA2354B2593","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"690EAAD012024CFEBD221AE40685140C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>If you have a hand-held probe in the chamber, open the flask and measure the pH and redox of the media and <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">record it in your lab book<\/span><span>. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075145,"guid":"FAF049F0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075144,"previous_guid":"F583E440278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0661CD383D164FC7AB72301209617B6A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A5832288CE0D43D5AE0EF7AA619A754D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dispense medium into Serum flasks or hungate tubes as needed. If media shows any precipitation, place it on a stirrer during dispension, so to ensure homogenous media. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075146,"guid":"FF193320278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075145,"previous_guid":"FAF049F0278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"79FEDFE12287417F858B58D9AF6713BF","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FC0C27A85A1B47718CFD53B29B0CEF6A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Seal tubes with butyl-rubber septa. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075147,"guid":"034D8E00278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075146,"previous_guid":"FF193320278411EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E6CBBBA23B61493889AA4F97B98E1D1F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B946C1140D324123814D9CB9D9C4A0C3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Place any remaining medium in a 1L Duran flask sealed with rubber butyl septa. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Label the flask with your initials, date, and the pH and redox measured in step 19<\/span><span>. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075148,"guid":"07A72420278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075147,"previous_guid":"034D8E00278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7E31896AEB1F4A9FAA5AF5C1C09274B2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"369FAC0CB70E46CF8BFA6E8B705D554F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Take media out of the anaerobic chamber and place aluminium crimp seals on the tubes you used. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075149,"guid":"104D7F20278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075148,"previous_guid":"07A72420278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A9FC450B74B04A83956E5112E66CF201","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"918014AB320546C3A79A668E3A8B1D08","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Autoclave media placed in flasks\/tubes in step 20, as well as media to be stored (from step 22). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075150,"guid":"15552F90278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075149,"previous_guid":"104D7F20278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5F1D1F77B95D41DC96365766B5506C94","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CE46BA7E61E04B98AEEF3120B84B4333","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Store in the dark and at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1D534730278611EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":80,"unit":"Room temperature","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"1A0D9158E9CF4720BFB00366C5732B86","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>IMPORTANT NOTE: Before using media for inoculation, the final component; Na<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>S should be added. This component is used for additional reducing of redox potential and also as Sulfur source. Its addition at this late stage of inoculation is because it is quite unstable and not ideal for storage. When adding Na<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>S, make sure you use the right amount for your culture volume (and given your stock solution concentration). <\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075151,"guid":"19A88420278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075150,"previous_guid":"15552F90278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"14A077F0EF604B548B105C8EAF01E36B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DE9F1341B49140EA86ED1D00C0B94569","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Any media that is older than 8 months should be discarded. Any stored media younger than 8 months can be used provided it has maintained its pH and redox in the required range. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1075152,"guid":"1DD60130278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","previous_id":1075151,"previous_guid":"19A88420278511EBA04DCF0145CC9FDA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D1AB8BE99195484E9E65B2EF6426481E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Dispense and finalise stage"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E79016696EEF4B27ADB6E9E55369EE2B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If possible, measure pH and redox in the anaerobic chamber before using any stored media. If the measurements are not within range (redox, below -300mV and pH, as defined by specific media) discard media and prepare new one. Do not attempt adjusting these values with media additions. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":1800,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This is a generic protocol for the preparation of <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">any<\/span><span> strictly anaerobic media. The exact media composition is assumed to be known by the user of this protocol (for example, we routinely use this protocol together with the media sheet; OSM01_01, available from OSS Lab website).<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1621958426}